\mathrm{cl}(A)=\bigcap \{F~\textrm{closed}:A\subseteq F\}
\mathrm{ncr}(A)=\bigcap_{g\in G}g^{-1}Ag
\begin{array}{cl} \mathrm{cl}(x) & = \bigcap \{F~\textrm{closed}:x\in F\} \\ & = \bigcap x\{x^{-1}F~\textrm{closed}:1_G\in x^{-1}F\} \\ & =x\bigcap\{E~\textrm{closed}:1_G\in E\} \\ & = x\,\mathrm{cl}(1)=xS \end{array}
\therefore~~ \mathrm{cl}(X)=\bigcup_{x\in X}\mathrm{cl}(x)=\bigcup_{x\in X}xS=XS.
